ğŸŒ Theoretical Learning
ğŸ”¸ TCP vs UDP

Explored the key difference between connection-oriented (TCP) and connectionless (UDP) protocols.

Learned their real-world use cases:

TCP: Reliable communication (HTTP, HTTPS, SSH, FTP)

UDP: Fast, lightweight, but less reliable (DNS, streaming, VoIP)

ğŸ”¸ How the Internet Works

Traced how data travels from a client through routers, DNS, and remote servers.

Understood how IP addresses, ports, and packets form the basis of data transfer.

